Class
All .java files
Members.java (class Member), Transaction.java, Contribution.java, Withdrawal.java, MotsheloManager.java, MainApp.java — each defines a distinct class.

Abstract Class
Transaction.java
'public abstract class Transaction' — cannot be instantiated directly; forces subclasses (Contribution, Withdrawal) to inherit its fields.

Inheritance
Contribution.java, Withdrawal.java
'public class Contribution extends Transaction' and 'public class Withdrawal extends Transaction' — both inherit amount, date, description and reuse the Transaction constructor via super().

Constructor
Transaction.java, Members.java, Contribution.java, Withdrawal.java
Transaction(double amount, String description), Member(String name, String omang), Contribution(double amount) calls super(amount, "Contribution"), Withdrawal(double amount) calls super(-amount, "Withdrawal").

Encapsulation
Members.java (class Member), Transaction.java
All fields declared private. Public getters: getName(), getOmang(), getBalance(), getHistory(), getAmount(), getDate(), getDescription() expose data safely.

Composition
Members.java (class Member)
'private ArrayList<Transaction> history' — Member owns its transaction list; the list does not exist independently of the Member object.

Polymorphism
Transaction.java, Contribution.java, Withdrawal.java
toString() is overridden in Transaction and used polymorphically. Contribution and Withdrawal objects are stored as Transaction references in the history ArrayList.

Method Overriding
Transaction.java
'@Override public String toString()' formats the transaction as a readable string; subclasses inherit this behaviour.

ArrayList / Collections
Members.java, MotsheloManager.java
'private ArrayList<Transaction> history' in Member; 'private List<Members> members' in MotsheloManager. Both use Java Collections Framework.

Static Method
MainApp.java
'private static void seedData(MotsheloManager manager)' is a static helper method called from main() without an object instance.

Object Instantiation
MainApp.java (seedData method)
new MotsheloManager(), new Members("Thapelo Kennedy", "123456789"), new Contribution(500.00) — objects created and used at runtime.

super() keyword
Contribution.java, Withdrawal.java
Contribution calls super(amount, "Contribution"); Withdrawal calls super(-amount, "Withdrawal") — passing arguments up to the parent constructor.
